First you need to take the @flank steak{2} out of your #fridge{} to bring it up to room temperature.

Pre-heat your #oven{} to 220 degrees and boil a #kettle{} of @water{150%ml}. Chop the @new potatoes{1} into small 2cm cubes, (no need to peel). Lightly crush the @black peppercorns{3/4%tbsp} in a #pestle and mortar{}. 

> Tip: If you don't have a pestle and mortar put them between two sheets of tinfoil and give them a little whack with a rolling pin.

Remove the @rosemary{1/2%sprig}(leaves removed) leaves from their stalks and chop very finely. Put your potatoes on a #baking tray{}, sprinkle over your rosemary leaves and drizzle over some @olive oil{}. Sprinkle over a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{}. Give the baking tray a good shake so your potatoes are evenly coated and cook on the top shelf of your oven for ~{30%minutes} until crispy (give the tray another shake halfway through cooking).

Peel and very finely chop the @echalion shallot{1/2}(peeled and finely chopped) and chop the @broccoli{1}(chopped into florets) into florets.

Put your broccoli florets on another baking tray, add a splash of @olive oil{}, a pinch of @salt{} and a good grind of @black pepper{} and pop in your oven on the middle shelf for ~{10%minutes} until slightly crispy.

Once your steak is at room temperature, season with a pinch of @salt{}. Heat a large #frying pan{} on high heat with a splash of @oil{}. When almost smoking, lay your steak in the pan and press it down.

> Tip: Lay the steak away from your body to stop oil spitting at you.

Cook for ~{3%minutes} on each side for medium cooked. Only turn your steak once and rest on a warm #plate{} when ready.

> Tip: Cook for a little longer if you like your steak well done.

Once your steak is removed from the pan, turn the heat to medium-low and add another small drizzle of @olive oil{} along with your shallot. Cook for ~{2%minutes} then add your peppercorns. After another ~{1%minute}, add your boiling water and stir in the @beef stock pot{1/2}.

Bubble away for a few mins until your sauce has reduced by half, take off the heat and stir in the @creme fraiche{1%tbsp}, this is your peppercorn sauce.

> Tip: For a decadent touch, add a small knob of butter at this point (if you have some).

Slice your steak diagonally into 1cm strips.

Serve your steak with a drizzle of peppercorn sauce and your crispy roasted rosemary potatoes and broccoli on the side.